The paper deals with the problem of sparse deconvolution, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of convex optimization techniques, which falls under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The problem of deconvolution is closely related to signal processing and image processing, which are covered by cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the solution, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning).
